    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="1168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1168">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.00/1990: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 20, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Your despatch No. 307, February 12.<note n="27" xml:id="d1168fn1">Not
                        printed. The Ambassador transmitted a communication from supporters of a
                        Panamanian presidential candidate requesting that the United States disarm
                        the National Police and supervise the elections to be held on June 2, 1940,
                        to insure fair elections.</note> This Government is determined by policy and
                    bound by treaty not to intervene directly or indirectly in the internal affairs
                    of Panama. Therefore, the supervision of the forthcoming elections or the
                    disarmament of the national police in connection with those elections are out of
                    the question.</p>
                <p>The Department agrees with you that no reply need be made to the communication
                    which you have already received or to others which you may receive in the
                    future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
